A prolonged dense freezing fog episode occurred mainly over the northern half of the CWA that lead to power bumps and scattered power outages due to the accumulation of rime ice on power lines. These power lines were stretched beyond their capacity. The episode finally ended with sunshine and milder temperatures, helping to melt the frost. Power companies did have to go out and manually clear some of the lines.
